The Hammer Tool can be found in /ws/margly/hammerhead/gqi and
/ws/margly/hammerhead/sdv

gqi options:
        -i IP address (1.2.3.4) 
        -n number of nullprocs (50)
        -P number of pings (50)
        -r number of RPCs (500,000)
        -t timeout (5000)
        -M number of session creation messages
        -p number of RPCs per print (100) 
        -b timing bucket size in milliseconds (5)
        -v verbose printfs
        -O number of output ports
        -k number of packet insertion cycles
        -F number of file cycles

commands:

createsession <ses_id> <in_prog_num> <out_prog_num> <in_port> <out_port>
              <bitrate> <mcast?> <dest_ip> <dest_udp>
              <src1_ip> <src2_ip> <src3_ip> <no_pid_remap?>

deletesession <ses_id>

createshell <ses_id> <port> <bitrate>

deleteshell <ses_id> <port>

bind <ses_id> <in_prog_num> <out_prog_num> <bitrate> <dest_ip> <dest_udp>
     <src1_ip> <src2_ip> <src3_ip> <no_pid_remap?>

unbind <ses_id>


